jobTitle: LuaFileSystem is a Lua library developed to complement the set of functions related to file systems offered by the standard Lua distribution.
LAR stands for Lua ARchive, and consist of a module and a file format that empowers a lua script to load lua modules from within a packaged, compressed file.
LuaZip is a lightweight Lua extension library used to read files stored inside zip files. The API is very similar to the standard Lua I/O library API.
LuaExpat is a SAX XML parser based on the Expat library.
